Gabrielle Dorziat https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gabrielle_Dorziat 0 Gabrielle Dorziat (1880–1979) was a French stage and film actress. Dorziat was a fashion trend setter in Paris and helped popularize the designs of Coco Chanel. The Théâtre Gabrielle-Dorziat in Épernay, France is named for her.
